text:
So, I know we’ve beaten CZ’s love of Flash effects into the ground, but I really wish they actually would’ve highlighted Sevinne with their upgrade episode. Their criticism is that they feel like Elsha runs it out of the box better, but the upgrade episode would’ve been a great avenue to explore how to make Sevinne more advantageous.

I’m not surprised at all, but after so much the stereotype becomes excessive.

I do kind of get where they were coming from on that, too, though... If you build Sevinne, its throwing a substantial amount of the deck out and replacing it with the best flashback/aftermath/retrace stuff you can find.

If there is something they don’t like they tend to get really dismissive of it. Lots of content creators do and don’t look at cards for what they are. They get to the lowest common denominator with legends and run with that “well X isn’t as powerful as Y so don’t run X” type stuff.
Never mind they do very different things and enable different strategies, but sure. Do your thing
It’s annoying when they’re the most listened to podcast about the format, folks take their words as gospel and they sometimes can invalidate commanders in the minds of the community with 2 sentences
We have that problem here as well, though. I see "X isn't as powerful as Y, so why would you run X" arguments on here all the time.

That was my issue with the whole thing. Elsha is obviously the “safest pick” out of the available commanders, but completely dismissing the other two isn’t cool. For what they were doing, I get it, but making people feel like trying to build Sevinne or Pramikon is a bad idea isn’t what you should be doing.
It’s why I had an issue with the graphic they used as their thumbnail
It's very disheartening to the casual players... which is supposed to be their only audience.
Don’t “X” off the other commanders, but put Elsha first. You can emphasize Elsha while not pulling the other two commanders down.
I think it's simply the $25 upgrade limit, if I'm being charitable.
I... don't buy that, honestly.
Flashback cards are *all* cheap.

Well, and that’s the thing, that makes sense, I get that, but talking about Sevinne and Pramikon like they’re the wrong choices *because* you have to put work into it is where I have the issue, that’s all.

They dismissed the other two because you can’t easily make a $25 upgrade and be done with it. For the context of the episode, it makes total sense, but you don’t need to crap on them because they aren’t as ubiquitous as Elsha.
I'll give you Sevinne, but is there anything in the deck as is that supports Pramikon?
I think that question is slightly going around the point Angelo is making.

No, and that’s what I’m saying. Elsha makes complete sense when doing $25 upgrades. I do not fault them for doing that. But talking about the other two like it’s a bad thing that they *can’t* be upgraded as easily is where my problem is, that’s all.
I’m not just posturing because my brand is literally Jeskai, they did that for the Madness deck too if I’m not mistaken, and I didn’t like it.

It’s a GREAT point, mind you, but it’s a matter of saying “this deck doesn’t support this archetype as well” vs. “Elsha is better for the deck.”

The change of language is important.
Yeah, it's a presentation issue for the most part.
But... wasn't that the point? It CAN'T be upgraded AS EASILY for $25?
My real problem is that its a presentation issue that is prevalent across EDH.
I'll give you that.
Pramikon probably couldn't be, easily.
Sevinne definitely could be.
But that isn’t a *bad* thing. Dismissing them because they aren’t as budget friendly isn’t inherently bad. Talking about them as if they aren’t worth it is the issue
There is a big difference to a newer player if they see these three images
Exactly.
Jack, if you're not careful you're gonna get my morning derailed trying to build budget Pramikon.
You don’t need to cross out any of the commanders, just out the one you’re focusing on first. It inherently makes the other two seem like the “wrong” choice to build in general.
I'm legitimately not certain if I'm being charitable, trying to see all sides of am issue, playing devil's advocate, or just being a troll.
Guiz, we shoodnt use casual. Is dizmizzive
That’s just for your daily dose of irony
:thinking_face:
There's plenty of cheap flicker and forced attack fodder. You could definitely upgrade Pramikon for $25.
It would be a lot more cards, but they're all penny-fodder.
That's true, Dean.
I’m currently building Pramikon flicker, and it may be a bit rough to win with on a budget. Purphoros is almost $30 now apparently
And the CK sponsorship doesn’t pay well on nickel cards when you upgrade the pramikon deck
Also, not to bring this to too <#CHA8U3W1H|hot-and-heavy> an area, but has anyone poked their head into the political realm this morning? It's literally on fire.

*Spoilers for Game Knights*


I don’t even think the budget is really the concern. They’re just over the moon with Flash-effects and that joke that they... just don’t look past it.

Josh won the precon pod episode with a bunch of Flashback synergy. River Kelpie, Burning Vengeance, etc etc. None of that really had to deal with Elsha.

The upgrade path to make Sevinne is really easy.
Goblin Electromancer
Mission Briefing
Goblin Dark Dwellers
Crackling Counterpart/ Quasiduplicate
Call the Skybreaker
Throes of Chaos
New Ral Zarek

Thats eight cards that you can get for under $10 total.
Please don't remind me about purphoros.
I buy listed it for roughly $6 back in the day.
It may not have been that much, even.
Blown out
As a thought exercise, I'm going to upgrade the deck to feature Pramikon for just $w5
Heh, Dean fell into the hole I was resisting.
This deck is fucking boss
Pramikon hooks another! >:D
I mean, Zedruu was my first Jeskai deck, and this is basically how I had Zedruu built. Pramikon just makes it a lot more consistent
